video_title: What Can You Do If Therapy Isn't Working?
transcript:
the last thing to do if you plateau in
therapy is simply find another therapist
this is something that I've done a lot
actually with my patients where if we're
stalling for a while we'll sit down and
I'll say okay like we're stalling it
seems like you're not making much much
progress let's think about how we want
to approach this we can try this we can
try this we can try this and we'll do
something like come up with a six-month
plan and at the end of those 6 months
we'll re-evaluate because not every
therapist knows everything and each
therapist has their own strengths and
weaknesses that they bring to the table
they have particular problems that
they're good at dealing with and
sometimes actually the best thing to do
if you're plateauing in therapy is to
try a different kind of therapy or try a
different therapist
